Qiwei Hu, Chenyu Huang, and others proposed InvisiReveal, a blockchain-based access control system that balances privacy and accountability in data sharing without centralized authorities37. Using a Blockchain-oriented Verifiable Commitment protocol and Zero-Knowledge Proofs, it enables anonymous access with traceable tags for identity revelation if needed. Their implementation verified access requests in under 5 milliseconds, showing practical efficiency. However, the system assumes honest user behavior during registration and relies on cooperation among blockchain nodes, which could limit its robustness in adversarial or resource-limited settings.Table 2
