As demonstrated in Table 10, our system’s multi-layered defense architecture achieves comprehensive resilience against 10 major blockchain attack vectors while maintaining immigration-specific safeguards. Unlike prior works that address isolated threats (e.g., Sybil resistance alone), we uniquely integrate cryptographic protections (post-quantum algorithms), consensus-layer hardening (PBFT with reputation scoring), and AI-driven anomaly detection-all while complying with GDPR and ICAO security standards. The framework’s efficacy is evidenced by its 100% attack detection rate during trials at Changi Airport, where it prevented 47 attempted exploits (including 3 novel AI-generated passport frauds) without false positives. Crucially, these security gains impose only 9.8% throughput overhead, a favorable tradeoff given the 400% improvement in mean-time-to-recovery compared to conventional border systems. This holistic approach sets a new benchmark for secure immigration blockchains.Table 10
