Transaction malleabilityAlter transaction signatures to create conflicting recordsAll transactions are secured with ECDSA-SECP384r1 signatures and W-OTS+ nonce binding. The document hashing protocol includes transaction metadata in the SHA-3-512 digest, making the complete request immutable once submitted to the mempool
Selfish miningWithhold blocks to gain unfair mining advantageOur modified PBFT incorporates a transparent block proposal pipeline where nodes must cryptographically prove they have not withheld blocks. The reputation system penalizes nodes with abnormal proposal gaps, and the dynamic leader rotation algorithm excludes suspected selfish miners
